{
  "text": "We now consider the four dimensional theory. Deleting node four in the above E 11 Dynkin diagram we find the subalgebra GL(4)\u2297E 7 and decomposing E 11 , and the l 1 representation, into this subalgebra we find the four dimensional theory. In this decomposition the positive level generators of E 11 are given by [ The generators at level three belong to the 56 = 28 + 28 and 912 = 420 + 36 + 420 + 36-dimensional representations of E 7 ; the decomposition is into representations of SL [CITATION_1] . The generator Z a 1 ,a 2 I 1 I 2 has no particular symmetry on its a 1 and a 2 indices. In the non-linear realisation these lead to the generalised space-time of the four dimensional theory which has the coordinates [21]",
